            <title>[DERBY-30] Connection.close() method inconsistently throws exception on closed connection</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-30</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;JDBC 3.0 Javadoc for java.sql.Connection.close() states&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Calling the method close on a Connection object that is already closed is a no-op.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In Derby embedded calling close on a closed connection from the DriverManager or EmbeddedDataSource incorrectly throws XJ012.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Calling close on a closed connection from a ConnectionPoolDataSource or XADataSource for Derby correctly returns correctly (no-op).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Similar issue for Statement.close() - needs to be a no-op on a closed Statement/PreparedStatement/CallableStatement&lt;/p&gt;</description>
